<p>CAM-DX is a CAD/CAM system that consists of a CAM engine based on CADmeister/CAM.</p><p>The CAM engine has been manufactured by C&amp;G SYSTEMS INC. a recognized company for machining resin molds.</p><p>CADmeister/CAM is a proven system for press die machining.</p><p>Thus, CAM-DX is a combination of high-speed and high-quality machining methods and conventional proven methods. It can respond to a wide variety of users&#39; needs.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h5><strong>Features</strong></h5><ul><li><u><strong>System Configuration</strong></u></li></ul><p>CAM-DX supports the machining modes: 2DCAM (hybrid 2D CAM), 3DCAM (hybrid 3D CAM) and 3DECAM (GP-CAM).</p><p>Thus, it can create paths that fit various types of machining such as holing in an assimilated environment of 2D and 3D machining.</p><p>Furthermore, the modelling capability of streamlining CAM operations as well as the capabilities of editing and analyzing surfaces improve the machining efficiency and the quality of paths.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_01.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><u><strong>3DECAM (GP-CAM)</strong></u></li></ul><p>3DECAM enables high-speed and high-quality machining due to CAM-TOOL engine (GP-CAM) supported by C&amp;G SYSTEMS INC. (which has an alliance with UEL Corporation.)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The &quot;Contour_Rough&quot; command</strong></p><p>Paths for roughly cutting contours of a modelled shape can be created on the cross sections, provided that the &quot;Offset&quot; command has been executed for the cross sections.</p><p>An efficient and safe rough machining is enabled due to inserting arcs in concave corners and inserting trochoid paths in heavily stressed portions.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_02.gif" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The &quot;Contour_Rough_Primary Machining&quot; command</strong></p><p>Any portions left uncut in the previous operation of roughly machining contours (hereinafter also referred to as &#39;Tohkoh So-kakoh&#39; in Japanese) can be automatically detected. Then, they are machined precisely along contour curves.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_03.gif" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The &quot;Contour_Finish&quot; command</strong></p><p>Finishing paths for machining the contour curves of a modelled shape can be created.</p><p>They also can be machined highly efficiently by executing this command which enables the capabilities of outputting Offset Paths for the gentle slopes where contour curves/lines run with a wide pitch in-between, moving between layers without air-cuts, and inserting arcs in concave corners.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_04.gif" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The &quot;Concave_Uncut Portion_Contour&quot; command</strong></p><p>This command can automatically detect any portions that have been left uncut by the previous operation, and create paths to make corners for the portions.</p><p>Safe operation without heavily stressing the tools is enabled through the consideration of settings for machining concaves and making corners through the use of arcs.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_05.gif" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The &quot;Concave_Uncut Portion&quot; command</strong></p><p>This command can automatically detect any portions that have been left uncut in the previous operation, and create paths to make corners along the ridges.</p><p>A highly efficient operation for making corners is enabled by this command which is capable of creating paths along contours on inclined surfaces and paths on gentle slope surfaces.</p><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_06.gif" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Other Methods of Machining</strong></p><p>3DECAM enables various methods of operation in order to meet shaping and machining requirements.</p><p>They are enabled by the commands :</p><ul><li>the &quot;Contour Rough - High efficiency&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Contour Scan&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Contour Finish - High quality&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Concave_Uncut Portion_High Quality&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Pencil&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Flat Offset&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Flat Scan&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Horizontal Area&quot; command.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><u><strong>Functions for CAM Modeling</strong></u></li></ul><p><strong>Correction of CAM Figures</strong></p><p>This category of functions to improve the quality of paths include the functions of filling in holes and creating support surfaces for machining. They are:</p><ul><li>the Form_FillingBase&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Form_FillingNotch&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;FillingLargeHole&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;CollecVertexDeletion&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;TopOp_AddBdCrv&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;One-time correction&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;AlignEndPnt&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;SrfEdgeExtension_Separate&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Create_FuzzyOffsetSurface&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;SectionalDieBandSurface&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;RemoveDupLines&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Curves unification&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;CompulsoryUniteCrv&quot; command.</li></ul><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_07.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>CAM Analysis</strong></p><p>CAM Analysis helps the confirmation of shapes and the calculations of paths in a phase of examining manufacturing processes. They are enabled by&nbsp;</p><ul><li>the &quot;Check_DuplicateSurfaces&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;SimpleUndercutCheck&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;ContainerBox&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Disp_HeightDim&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;FigureRetrieval&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;GeomCheck&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;ConvertToFreeSrf&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;ConvertToAnalyticSrf&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;Reduce_BaseSrf&quot; command.</li></ul><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_08.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>CAM Dimensions and Annotations</strong></p><p>The functions of &#39;CAM Dimensions and Annotations&#39; display dimensions of shapes and 3D annotation data and also output them in machining instruction manuals and so on. They are performed by the commands:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>the &quot;RefDim_Create&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;RefDim_DispON&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;RefDim_DispOFF&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_Create&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_Change&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_Delete&quot;&nbsp;command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_Move&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_ChgProperty&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_DispON&quot; command</li><li>the &quot;3DAnnotation_DispOFF&quot; command.</li></ul><p><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" alt="" src="https://uelthai.co.th/uploads/product/4.CAM/3.CAM-DX/CAM_DX_09.jpg" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p><br></p><h5><br></h5><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p>